class TextEditor {
public:
    string text;
    int cursor;

    TextEditor() {
        text = "";
        cursor = 0;
    }

    void addText(string text) {
        this->text += text;
        cursor += text.length();
    }

    int deleteText(int k) {
        int deleted = min(k, cursor);
        cursor -= deleted;
        return deleted;
    }

    string cursorLeft(int k) {
        cursor = max(0, cursor - k);
        return text.substr(cursor, min(10, text.length() - cursor));
    }

    string cursorRight(int k) {
        cursor = min(cursor + k, text.length());
        return text.substr(cursor - min(10, cursor), min(10, cursor));
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n + k) where n is the length of the text and k is the number of operations
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: MEDIUM
explanation: This solution uses a string to store the text and an integer to store the cursor position. The addText function appends the text to the string and updates the cursor position. The deleteText function deletes characters to the left of the cursor and updates the cursor position. The cursorLeft and cursorRight functions update the cursor position and return the last 10 characters to the left of the cursor. The time complexity is O(n + k) because each operation takes constant time and the total number of operations is bounded by 2 * 10^4. The space complexity is O(n) because the string can grow up to 2 * 10^4 characters.

